{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What They Are"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Both stemming and lemmatization are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "word normalisation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " techniques. Their shared goal is to map different inflected forms of the same word to a single base form so that a model sees \"run\", \"running\", and \"ran\" as related rather than three unrelated tokens."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Technique"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Speed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stemming"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rule-based suffix stripping (no dictionary)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A stem — may not be a real word (e.g. \"studi\", \"car\" from \"caring\")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very fast (~1 μs/word)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lemmatization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Morphological analysis + vocabulary dictionary + POS tag"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A lemma — always a valid dictionary headword (e.g. \"study\", \"care\", \"good\" from \"better\")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slower (model + dict lookup)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Side-by-Side Examples"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Table comparing Porter Stemmer output vs spaCy Lemmatizer output for: running, ran, studies, caring, better, wolves, fairly — showing over-stemming errors and irregular forms the lemmatizer handles correctly"}}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Over-stemming:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " The Porter Stemmer reduces \"caring\" to \"car\" because it strips \"-ing\" and then \"-e\" via rule. The stem \"car\" collides with the noun \"car\" — two completely unrelated concepts now share the same form. This is a real vocabulary collision that silently corrupts features."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stemming"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A stemmer applies a deterministic sequence of suffix-stripping rules. The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Porter Stemmer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Martin Porter, 1980) is the most widely used English stemmer. It runs five ordered rule steps, each shortening the word by removing one suffix if a structural condition holds. For example, step 1a replaces \"-sses\" with \"-ss\" and \"-ies\" with \"-i\"."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NLTK ships three stemmers:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "PorterStemmer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — classic, well-understood"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "SnowballStemmer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — Porter's improved successor; supports 15+ languages"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "LancasterStemmer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — very aggressive; produces shorter stems but more collisions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install nltk\nimport nltk\nfrom nltk.stem import PorterStemmer, SnowballStemmer\n\nnltk.download('punkt_tab', quiet=True)\n\nporter = PorterStemmer()\nsnowball = SnowballStemmer('english')\n\nwords = ['running', 'ran', 'studies', 'caring', 'better', 'wolves']\n\nfor w in words:\n    print(f\"{w:12} → porter: {porter.stem(w):10} snowball: {snowball.stem(w)}\")\n\n# running     → porter: run        snowball: run\n# ran         → porter: ran        snowball: ran\n# studies     → porter: studi      snowball: studi\n# caring      → porter: car        snowball: car\n# better      → porter: better     snowball: better\n# wolves      → porter: wolv       snowball: wolv"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lemmatization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A lemmatizer uses a morphological vocabulary (e.g. WordNet) to map each inflected form to its "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "lemma"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the dictionary headword. Because it knows that \"ran\" is the past tense of \"run\" and \"better\" is the comparative of \"good\", it produces linguistically correct base forms even for irregular words."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lemmatization requires knowing the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "part-of-speech (POS) tag"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to look up the correct entry. The word \"saw\" has different lemmas as a verb (\"see\") and a noun (\"saw\")."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NLTK WordNetLemmatizer"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import nltk\nfrom nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\nfrom nltk.corpus import wordnet\n\nnltk.download('wordnet', quiet=True)\nnltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger_eng', quiet=True)\n\nlemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n\n# Without POS: defaults to noun — wrong for verbs\nprint(lemmatizer.lemmatize('running'))         # running  (noun default)\nprint(lemmatizer.lemmatize('running', pos='v'))# run      (correct)\nprint(lemmatizer.lemmatize('studies', pos='v'))# study\nprint(lemmatizer.lemmatize('better', pos='a')) # good     (adjective comparative)\nprint(lemmatizer.lemmatize('wolves'))          # wolf     (noun plural — works without POS)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "To avoid specifying POS manually, NLTK's POS tagger can fill it in automatically:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from nltk import pos_tag, word_tokenize\n\ndef get_wordnet_pos(treebank_tag: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Map Penn Treebank POS tag to WordNet POS constant.\"\"\"\n    if treebank_tag.startswith('J'):\n        return wordnet.ADJ\n    elif treebank_tag.startswith('V'):\n        return wordnet.VERB\n    elif treebank_tag.startswith('R'):\n        return wordnet.ADV\n    else:\n        return wordnet.NOUN\n\ndef lemmatize_sentence(sentence: str) -> list[str]:\n    tokens = word_tokenize(sentence.lower())\n    tagged = pos_tag(tokens)\n    return [\n        lemmatizer.lemmatize(word, pos=get_wordnet_pos(tag))\n        for word, tag in tagged\n    ]\n\nprint(lemmatize_sentence(\"The wolves were running faster than he had expected\"))\n# ['the', 'wolf', 'be', 'run', 'fast', 'than', 'he', 'have', 'expect']"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spaCy Lemmatization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spaCy performs POS tagging and lemmatization together in one pass — no separate step needed:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install spacy && python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm\nimport spacy\n\nnlp = spacy.load('en_core_web_sm')\n\ndoc = nlp(\"The wolves were running faster than he had expected\")\nfor token in doc:\n    print(f\"{token.text:12} → {token.lemma_:12} ({token.pos_})\")\n\n# The          → the          (DET)\n# wolves       → wolf         (NOUN)\n# were         → be           (AUX)\n# running      → run          (VERB)\n# faster       → fast         (ADV)\n# than         → than         (SCONJ)\n# he           → he           (PRON)\n# had          → have         (AUX)\n# expected     → expect       (VERB)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use Each"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Situation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reason"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TF-IDF / bag-of-words"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stemming"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Speed matters; stem collisions are acceptable; output is never shown to users"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Topic modelling, keyword extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lemmatization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Topic keywords are shown to users — they must be recognisable words, not truncated stems"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large-scale search index (millions of docs)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stemming"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Throughput: stemming processes millions of words per second; lemmatization is ~10–50× slower"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NLP pipeline needing linguistic accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lemmatization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correct base forms avoid false matches (\"caring\" ≠ \"car\") and handle irregular forms"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BERT, GPT, Llama fine-tuning or inference"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neither"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Subword tokenizers handle morphological variation automatically; stemming/lemmatization before a Transformer discards inflection signals the model was trained to use"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Two Classic Failure Modes"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Over-stemming"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": two unrelated words produce the same stem. Classic example: \"caring\" → \"car\" (Porter), \"general\" → \"gener\" (Porter) which also matches \"generous\" → \"gener\". The model conflates unrelated concepts."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Under-stemming"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": related words do not reach the same stem. Example: \"run\" and \"ran\" stay as \"run\" and \"ran\" under all three NLTK stemmers because the irregular past tense requires dictionary knowledge the stemmer lacks."}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lemmatization eliminates both: it uses a dictionary to handle irregular forms (no under-stemming) and never conflates unrelated words (no over-stemming)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Stemming"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a fast, rule-based suffix stripper — suitable when throughput matters and linguistic accuracy is secondary (e.g. TF-IDF for large-scale search)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lemmatization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " uses a vocabulary dictionary and POS tagging to produce valid dictionary headwords — essential when the normalised form is displayed to users or when irregular forms matter"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Porter Stemmer can "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "over-stem"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — mapping unrelated words to the same stem (\"caring\" → \"car\"). Always check examples from your actual corpus before committing to a stemmer."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spaCy's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "token.lemma_"}, {"type": "text", "text": " attribute is the easiest production path — POS tagging and lemmatization happen in the same pipeline pass"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neither technique is needed for Transformer models"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — BERT and GPT use subword tokenization which naturally collapses related forms, and they were pre-trained on unprocessed text where tense and plurality carry meaning"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NLTK's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "WordNetLemmatizer"}, {"type": "text", "text": " requires the POS tag to be passed explicitly; without it, it defaults to noun and produces wrong results for verbs (\"running\" → \"running\" instead of \"run\")"}]}]}]}]}}